#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:2
msgid "Automatically managing remote sources with `npins`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:4
msgid ""
"The Nix language can be used to describe dependencies between files managed "
"by Nix. Nix expressions themselves can depend on remote sources, and there "
"are multiple ways to specify their origin, as shown in [](pinning-nixpkgs)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:7
msgid ""
"For more automation around handling remote sources, set up [`npins`](https://"
"github.com/andir/npins/) in your project:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:9
msgid ""
"$ nix-shell -p npins --run \"npins init --bare; npins add github nixos "
"nixpkgs --branch nixos-23.11\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:13
msgid ""
"This command will fetch the latest revision of the Nixpkgs 23.11 release "
"branch. In the current directory it will generate `npins/sources.json`, "
"which will contain a pinned reference to the obtained revision. It will also "
"create `npins/default.nix`, which exposes those dependencies as an attribute "
"set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:17
msgid ""
"Import the generated `npins/default.nix` as the default value for the "
"argument to the function in `default.nix` and use it to refer to the Nixpkgs "
"source directory:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:19
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  sources ? import ./npins,\n"
"  system ? builtins.currentSystem,\n"
"  pkgs ? import sources.nixpkgs { inherit system; config = {}; overlays = "
"[]; },\n"
"}:\n"
"{\n"
"  package = pkgs.hello;\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:30
msgid ""
"`nix-build` will call the top-level function with the empty attribute set `{}"
"`, or with the attributes passed via [`--arg`](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/"
"stable/command-ref/nix-build#opt-arg) or [`--argstr`](https://nix.dev/manual/"
"nix/stable/command-ref/nix-build#opt-argstr). This pattern allows "
"[overriding remote sources](overriding-sources-npins) programmatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:33
msgid ""
"Add `npins` to the development environment for your project to have it "
"readily available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:35
msgid ""
" {\n"
"   sources ? import ./npins,\n"
"   system ? builtins.currentSystem,\n"
"   pkgs ? import sources.nixpkgs { inherit system; config = {}; overlays = "
"[]; },\n"
" }:\n"
"-{\n"
"+rec {\n"
"   package = pkgs.hello;\n"
"+  shell = pkgs.mkShellNoCC {\n"
"+    inputsFrom = [ package ];\n"
"+    packages = with pkgs; [\n"
"+      npins\n"
"+    ];\n"
"+  };\n"
" }\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:53
msgid "Also add a `shell.nix` to enter that environment more conveniently:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:55
msgid "(import ./. {}).shell\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:59
msgid ""
"See [](./sharing-dependencies) for details, and note that here you have to "
"pass an empty attribute set to the imported expression, since `default.nix` "
"now contains a function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:62
msgid "Overriding sources"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:64
msgid ""
"As an example, we will use the previously created expression with an older "
"version of Nixpkgs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:66
msgid ""
"Enter the development environment, create a new directory, and set up npins "
"with a different version of Nixpkgs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:68
msgid ""
"$ nix-shell\n"
"[nix-shell]$ mkdir old\n"
"[nix-shell]$ cd old\n"
"[nix-shell]$ npins init --bare\n"
"[nix-shell]$ npins add github nixos nixpkgs --branch nixos-21.11\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:76
msgid ""
"Create a file `default.nix` in the new directory to import the original one "
"with the `sources` you just created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:78
msgid "import ../default.nix { sources = import ./npins; }\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:82
msgid "This will result in a different version being built:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:84
msgid ""
"$ nix-build -A build\n"
"$ ./result/bin/hello --version | head -1\n"
"hello (GNU Hello) 2.10\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:90
msgid "Sources can also be overridden on the command line:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:92
msgid "nix-build .. -A build --arg sources 'import ./npins'\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:96
msgid "Migrating from `niv`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:98
msgid ""
"A previous version of this guide recommended using [`niv`](https://github."
"com/nmattia/niv/), a similar pin manager written in Haskell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:100
msgid ""
"If you have a project using `niv`, you can import remote source definitions "
"into `npins`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:102
msgid "npins import-niv\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/dependency-management.md:107
msgid ""
"All the imported entries will be updated, so they won't necessarily point to "
"the same commits as before!"
msgstr ""

